Team Kenya for Tokyo Games to begin training in Nairobi bubble from MondayNow it is off, now it is on first leg of AK track and field series blasts off at 8.30am SaturdayTergat said NOC-K will work with the team to ensure outstanding results are achieved. The 2018 World Under-20 5,000m silver medallist Stanley Waithaka headline the first leg of Athletics Kenya Track and Field meeting this weekend at the Nyayo National Stadium. 

It will be the youngster’s first race this season. He  last competitive race was 10,000m at the Nittadai Distance Meet in Yokohama, Japan on December 5, that he won in 27:48.27. 



